The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said it had administered 5 919 418 first doses of COVID-19 vaccines in the country as of Thursday morning and distributed 21 419 800 doses. The tally of vaccine doses distributed and the number of people who received the first dose are for both Moderna and Pfizer/BioNTech, vaccines as of 9:00 a.m. ET on Thursday, the agency said. According to the tally posted on January 6, the agency had administered 5 306 797 first doses of the vaccines and distributed 17 288 950 doses. A total of 3 770 425 vaccine doses were distributed for use on long-term care facilities and 603 313 people in the facilities got their first dose, the agency said.